WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.733
[LUNA] Everyone,
this is Edward Arellano.

00:00:04.333 --> 00:00:06.400
[KIKO] Okay.
Welcome to Hotel 88.

00:00:06.533 --> 00:00:08.000
[JADE] Don't you really
know anything?

00:00:08.133 --> 00:00:09.667
[KIKO] Why?
What else don't I know

00:00:09.800 --> 00:00:11.767
- about my family?
- Please, just don't bother me!

00:00:11.900 --> 00:00:13.100
- Don't go after me!
- Jade!

00:00:13.233 --> 00:00:16.133
Even when it comes to Edward,
she wants to get ahead.

00:00:16.267 --> 00:00:17.133
Luna's really something,
isn't she?

00:00:17.267 --> 00:00:19.700
[MARTIN] Wait.
Do you have a past?

00:00:19.833 --> 00:00:21.300
We do.

00:00:21.433 --> 00:00:22.267
What?

00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:23.933
[GIO] Music festival.
They're right.

00:00:24.067 --> 00:00:24.967
There are lots of returns.

00:00:25.100 --> 00:00:26.400
I can make this event happen.

00:00:26.533 --> 00:00:27.600
But, can you?

00:00:27.733 --> 00:00:28.600
[LUNA] Are you kidding me?

00:00:28.733 --> 00:00:29.967
If the hotel loses money,

00:00:30.100 --> 00:00:31.133
I will make you pay.

00:00:31.267 --> 00:00:34.233
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:36.200
You want to open up
that family's case?

00:00:36.333 --> 00:00:38.033
I just need solid evidence.

00:00:38.167 --> 00:00:40.200
Sir Henri! Good morning.

00:00:45.500 --> 00:00:48.500
Good morning, Leon,
Mrs. Almazan.

00:00:49.467 --> 00:00:50.733
Good morning.

00:00:50.867 --> 00:00:52.933
Is there a problem?

00:00:53.267 --> 00:00:54.600
[HENRI] Oh, Leon!

00:00:54.867 --> 00:00:56.167
As police officers,

00:00:56.300 --> 00:00:58.100
we never run out of problems.

00:00:58.633 --> 00:01:01.733
All the problems in
our town are also our burden.

00:01:02.367 --> 00:01:03.800
Oh, sir.

00:01:04.367 --> 00:01:06.667
If you burden yourself with
other people's problems...

00:01:07.267 --> 00:01:09.800
doesn't that just mean
that you're a meddler?

00:01:09.933 --> 00:01:11.767
But that's how the police are.

00:01:11.900 --> 00:01:13.400
We meddle in things...

00:01:13.733 --> 00:01:15.267
because we care.

00:01:15.400 --> 00:01:18.000
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:18.133 --> 00:01:21.033
Leon, can we go now?

00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:23.833
We'll get going then.

00:01:24.167 --> 00:01:25.433
Okay.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:27.333
Take care.

00:01:30.567 --> 00:01:32.767
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

00:01:32.900 --> 00:01:39.133
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:01:39.267 --> 00:01:40.500
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

00:01:46.933 --> 00:01:53.767
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:08.900 --> 00:02:15.733
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:02:30.933 --> 00:02:37.767
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:02:46.233 --> 00:02:47.467
[LUNA] No.

00:02:47.633 --> 00:02:48.700
No...

00:02:50.100 --> 00:02:51.200
No.

00:02:51.333 --> 00:02:53.700
You're rejecting all
my suggestions for the DJ?

00:02:53.833 --> 00:02:55.867
[LUNA] I'm rejecting them
because they're all expensive.

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:58.600
But we'll get that money back
with the ticket sales!

00:02:58.733 --> 00:02:59.833
It's still expensive!

00:02:59.967 --> 00:03:01.433
You'll have to pay for their
transportation from Manila!

00:03:01.567 --> 00:03:02.400
There are a lot of
local artists here.

00:03:02.533 --> 00:03:03.633
Why don't you get them instead?

00:03:03.767 --> 00:03:04.633
I've included them there!

00:03:04.767 --> 00:03:06.467
But the lineup has
to be balanced.

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:08.133
You don't even want
Echo Nova to come?

00:03:08.267 --> 00:03:09.467
You like them, don't you?

00:03:09.933 --> 00:03:11.000
It's expensive!

00:03:11.133 --> 00:03:12.333
Do you want someone affordable?

00:03:12.467 --> 00:03:14.267
Then go and perform yourself
so it'd be free.

00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:17.200
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:17.333 --> 00:03:19.533
What's wrong with you, Gio?

00:03:22.633 --> 00:03:24.100
I'm just trying to
be practical because

00:03:24.233 --> 00:03:27.067
I want to please
my general manager.

00:03:27.200 --> 00:03:28.800
And it's true that
you're really smart!

00:03:29.267 --> 00:03:30.267
So you can go do it, DJ--

00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:32.533
If you really want the people
on your list...

00:03:32.933 --> 00:03:34.200
then negotiate again.

00:03:34.333 --> 00:03:37.733
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:03:37.867 --> 00:03:38.767
Fine!

00:03:38.900 --> 00:03:40.767
I'll come back to you
for a second proposal!

00:03:46.900 --> 00:03:52.333
[MUSIC TURNS UPBEAT]

00:03:52.467 --> 00:03:55.133
[FEMALE EMCEE] Bringing sweet,
new energy to the floor...

00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:57.400
DJ Solenn!

00:03:59.333 --> 00:04:01.700
Good evening!

00:04:01.833 --> 00:04:08.800
- [CROWD CHANTING]
- [UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:04:23.933 --> 00:04:27.167
[UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:04:27.300 --> 00:04:28.533
It's Luna.

00:04:28.700 --> 00:04:35.567
[CROWD CHEERING]

00:04:42.367 --> 00:04:43.467
Luna!

00:04:43.600 --> 00:04:45.233
[LUNA] Oh, sure. Come on.

00:04:46.200 --> 00:04:47.167
Luna!

00:04:47.300 --> 00:04:48.467
[MAN] Can we do the other side?

00:04:49.567 --> 00:04:51.200
- Thank you. Thank you!
- Thank you.

00:04:51.333 --> 00:04:52.533
[GIO] Luna!

00:04:53.267 --> 00:04:54.767
- Thank you.
- Luna!

00:04:55.233 --> 00:04:56.433
It's Gio!

00:04:56.567 --> 00:04:57.500
Gio!

00:04:57.933 --> 00:04:59.067
- Gio?
- Gio!

00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:00.800
Gio!

00:05:01.200 --> 00:05:02.967
[LUNA] Hello! It's really you!

00:05:03.100 --> 00:05:08.267
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:09.300
[LUNA] Long time!

00:05:09.433 --> 00:05:11.467
- I know.
- [LUNA CHUCKLES]

00:05:16.067 --> 00:05:17.267
Hi, DJ!

00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:18.700
- Hi! Hello!
- Hi, DJ!

00:05:18.833 --> 00:05:25.800
["TADHANA" BY
SOFRONIO VASQUEZ PLAYING]

00:05:26.967 --> 00:05:28.700
You're here again.

00:05:28.833 --> 00:05:31.400
Are you going
to come here every night?

00:05:32.433 --> 00:05:34.533
As long as you're here,
I'll be here.

00:05:40.933 --> 00:05:47.800
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:06:02.933 --> 00:06:09.800
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:06:17.933 --> 00:06:18.900
[GIO] Same spot.

00:06:19.033 --> 00:06:20.067
[LUNA] Same spot!

00:06:23.933 --> 00:06:24.933
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:06:25.067 --> 00:06:26.300
Wait!

00:06:26.433 --> 00:06:27.533
What is it?

00:06:27.667 --> 00:06:29.833
The club's dirty!
You should clean up first.

00:06:29.967 --> 00:06:31.133
I'm already used to it.

00:06:31.267 --> 00:06:32.633
[GIO] Even so.

00:06:33.433 --> 00:06:36.167
You should still be clean.

00:06:36.600 --> 00:06:38.033
- Okay?
- Okay.

00:06:38.167 --> 00:06:39.200
[GIO] Eat up.

00:06:39.333 --> 00:06:43.233
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:06:43.400 --> 00:06:44.433
I already told you that

00:06:44.567 --> 00:06:46.833
we could eat somewhere else
after your gig.

00:06:47.500 --> 00:06:49.133
I like it here.

00:06:49.267 --> 00:06:50.400
It's already my ritual.

00:06:50.533 --> 00:06:53.833
Cup noodles every day,
with you.

00:06:55.933 --> 00:06:58.767
If only those who know you
from our town can see you now.

00:06:58.900 --> 00:06:59.800
Mm!

00:06:59.933 --> 00:07:01.267
They have no idea.

00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:03.233
That's why
you should say nothing.

00:07:04.067 --> 00:07:06.200
You haven't been there
for over a year!

00:07:06.333 --> 00:07:08.633
Do they still know who
Luna Almazan is?

00:07:08.767 --> 00:07:10.233
They know who Luna is.

00:07:10.367 --> 00:07:13.833
But they don't know Solenn!

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:20.833
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:07:30.867 --> 00:07:33.433
I wish we could
always be like this.

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:39.567
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:07:39.700 --> 00:07:40.900
[GIO] We could do that.

00:07:42.400 --> 00:07:44.133
Just say it.

00:07:53.700 --> 00:08:00.767
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:08:15.700 --> 00:08:22.733
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:08:37.800 --> 00:08:39.633
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

00:08:39.767 --> 00:08:42.467
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

00:08:42.600 --> 00:08:43.833
[LUNA CHUCKLES]

00:08:59.700 --> 00:09:02.333
Alright. I've introduced you
to our clients, okay?

00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:06.800
We're going to our
laundry supplier next.

00:09:08.133 --> 00:09:10.400
Also, the, uh...

00:09:11.100 --> 00:09:13.967
Can you put the coconut tree
at the entrance to the back?

00:09:14.300 --> 00:09:16.100
- Got it?
- Yes.

00:09:16.967 --> 00:09:18.233
Hey, Kiko.

00:09:18.433 --> 00:09:21.500
I just asked you to move a tree
and you said yes.

00:09:22.033 --> 00:09:23.100
Are you okay?

00:09:23.467 --> 00:09:24.967
I'm sorry.

00:09:26.233 --> 00:09:29.067
Is it because of Jade
and the mysterious earring?

00:09:30.133 --> 00:09:33.000
Give me a hip, a belly,
and a pork chop, please.

00:09:34.133 --> 00:09:36.000
What really happened?

00:09:36.200 --> 00:09:38.067
Why did you grow apart?

00:09:39.067 --> 00:09:40.533
I don't know, either.

00:09:41.200 --> 00:09:43.300
She just suddenly
stopped talking to me.

00:09:43.300 --> 00:09:44.800
Did you ask why?

00:09:45.500 --> 00:09:48.033
She said we're not kids anymore.

00:09:48.500 --> 00:09:50.533
That a lot has changed.

00:09:51.067 --> 00:09:54.100
Does that mean
we can't be friends anymore?

00:09:54.967 --> 00:09:56.167
Well, it's not like that.

00:09:56.167 --> 00:10:02.000
But right now, Jade is focused
on your family affairs.

00:10:03.333 --> 00:10:04.300
You know what I think?

00:10:04.300 --> 00:10:07.033
I think you should focus
on the music fest.

00:10:07.233 --> 00:10:10.500
If it goes well,
the hotel will be successful.

00:10:11.100 --> 00:10:12.867
And the hotel's success

00:10:13.467 --> 00:10:16.867
will be a way for you
to make amends.

00:10:17.367 --> 00:10:18.267
Okay?

00:10:18.267 --> 00:10:20.133
- Is it done?
- [VENDOR] Yes, ma'am.

00:10:29.433 --> 00:10:31.200
- [BOY 1] Miss Jade!
- [GIRL 1] Miss Jade!

00:10:33.133 --> 00:10:34.267
Miss Jade!

00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:37.433
Wow! You all look very excited.

00:10:37.433 --> 00:10:39.167
Have you been waiting for me?

00:10:39.167 --> 00:10:40.633
- Yes!
- [GIGGLES]

00:10:40.633 --> 00:10:43.067
- Come on.
- Are we going to begin?

00:10:43.067 --> 00:10:45.567
Yeah, I'm just going
to get our materials ready,

00:10:45.567 --> 00:10:47.600
then we'll start right away.

00:10:47.600 --> 00:10:49.200
Miss Jade, this is for you.

00:10:49.533 --> 00:10:51.233
- It's a steamed bun.
- Wow! Steamed buns!

00:10:51.233 --> 00:10:52.600
- Did you get my favorite?
- Yes.

00:10:52.600 --> 00:10:54.967
Wow! Thank you, Boyet!

00:10:54.967 --> 00:10:57.267
You're all so sweet!
Here, let's share.

00:10:57.467 --> 00:10:58.933
- Thank you.
- [GIGGLES]

00:10:58.933 --> 00:11:00.267
- Miss Jade...
- Mm?

00:11:00.267 --> 00:11:04.433
Is Sir Edward coming, too?

00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:07.000
Ah... [CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:10.133
I don't think he can come today.

00:11:10.167 --> 00:11:12.967
Looks like he's busy
with other things right now.

00:11:14.567 --> 00:11:15.633
- Let's go.
- Let's go!

00:11:17.367 --> 00:11:19.067
Oh, Boyet!

00:11:19.267 --> 00:11:22.233
Oh, no! You got the wrapper.

00:11:22.233 --> 00:11:25.133
[LAUGHING] It's because
you're eating too fast.

00:11:25.133 --> 00:11:27.167
Here, I'll take it off for you.

00:11:27.167 --> 00:11:28.933
Now, open wide. Aah!

00:11:28.933 --> 00:11:30.133
Mm!

00:11:30.133 --> 00:11:32.433
- It looks so good.
- [LAUGHS]

00:11:32.433 --> 00:11:34.333
Come on. Are you guys
excited to paint?

00:11:34.633 --> 00:11:35.667
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:11:35.667 --> 00:11:37.433
You don't sound like it.

00:11:41.200 --> 00:11:42.300
[CHUCKLES]

00:11:42.567 --> 00:11:44.400
Is that really
what you're going to eat?

00:11:44.633 --> 00:11:46.700
Am I starving you here?

00:11:48.267 --> 00:11:49.500
It's just good, Dad.

00:11:50.033 --> 00:11:51.033
You want a bite?

00:11:52.400 --> 00:11:53.400
All yours.

00:11:55.967 --> 00:11:57.267
By the way,

00:11:57.967 --> 00:12:00.200
do you have a schedule today
in the community or...

00:12:00.200 --> 00:12:01.233
are you just not gonna go?

00:12:02.333 --> 00:12:04.600
No, Dad. I have another meeting.

00:12:06.500 --> 00:12:09.700
Okay. Is this for your
Hotel 88 promotions?

00:12:11.533 --> 00:12:13.600
Yeah. Just an update meeting.

00:12:14.300 --> 00:12:17.267
I've hired people
to handle the guestlist

00:12:17.300 --> 00:12:19.367
for the festival.

00:12:20.433 --> 00:12:21.733
Good.

00:12:21.733 --> 00:12:25.467
I like that you're taking the
Hotel 88 promotion seriously.

00:12:27.633 --> 00:12:29.600
It's just like you said.

00:12:30.467 --> 00:12:32.233
If you choose to do the work,

00:12:33.433 --> 00:12:35.167
then do it perfectly.

00:12:35.667 --> 00:12:36.633
Correct.

00:12:37.267 --> 00:12:38.500
Also...

00:12:40.400 --> 00:12:43.333
This is important to Jade,
so might as well...

00:12:45.200 --> 00:12:46.600
Mm, okay. [CHUCKLES]

00:12:46.600 --> 00:12:48.633
Might as well because
it's important to Jade.

00:12:49.300 --> 00:12:50.333
There it is.

00:12:50.533 --> 00:12:52.567
There. I see it.
Do you see that?

00:12:53.333 --> 00:12:56.267
I can see that Jade
is the real reason

00:12:56.267 --> 00:12:58.600
why you're taking
this job seriously.

00:12:59.033 --> 00:13:01.000
No way, Dad. Come on.

00:13:01.800 --> 00:13:03.433
No way? Hm?

00:13:03.633 --> 00:13:05.133
You sure it's all business?

00:13:05.133 --> 00:13:06.600
Of course, it's just business.

00:13:07.633 --> 00:13:08.767
What else?

00:13:10.333 --> 00:13:13.733
And I know this is important
to you, too.

00:13:13.733 --> 00:13:18.067
So, it's good that
I get to do this so, you know...

00:13:18.600 --> 00:13:22.600
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYS]

00:13:23.400 --> 00:13:24.633
Okay.

00:13:25.267 --> 00:13:28.433
If it's really just business,
then, good job.

00:13:29.200 --> 00:13:30.233
Keep it up.

00:13:30.500 --> 00:13:31.533
And, uh...

00:13:32.267 --> 00:13:34.100
Good job on your heart.

00:13:34.100 --> 00:13:36.667
[SNICKERS]

00:13:39.767 --> 00:13:41.200
Give me a break, Dad.

00:13:47.133 --> 00:13:49.700
Excuse me. Has Jade come in?

00:13:49.700 --> 00:13:50.767
I don't know, sir.

00:13:51.233 --> 00:13:52.333
Alright, thank you.

00:14:03.500 --> 00:14:04.633
[PHONE BLEEPS]

00:14:07.733 --> 00:14:08.733
Huh?

00:14:09.633 --> 00:14:10.800
She blocked me?

00:14:12.867 --> 00:14:19.800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:14:22.533 --> 00:14:24.333
You will need to check
with the tourism officer

00:14:24.333 --> 00:14:26.167
if we need to register
with them

00:14:26.167 --> 00:14:28.767
if people are going here
for the music festival.

00:14:28.800 --> 00:14:30.433
You also need to
arrange a meeting with

00:14:30.433 --> 00:14:32.567
the city hall if we need
security.

00:14:32.567 --> 00:14:33.767
Sir?

00:14:33.767 --> 00:14:35.767
Is your middle initial
the letter "U"?

00:14:36.533 --> 00:14:40.467
No, "S" for Sandoval.
Do they need that in the permit?

00:14:40.467 --> 00:14:42.633
I thought it was
the letter "U"...

00:14:42.633 --> 00:14:44.700
U for... utusero (bossy)!

00:14:44.700 --> 00:14:47.667
[RAPHIE] Sir! You've dropped
so many orders!

00:14:47.667 --> 00:14:49.133
I did not sign up for this job!

00:14:50.067 --> 00:14:51.367
You are a hotel staff.

00:14:52.233 --> 00:14:53.533
I'm counting on you.

00:14:54.500 --> 00:14:56.567
Uh, sir.

00:14:56.567 --> 00:14:58.633
My job is in food
and beverage.

00:14:59.667 --> 00:15:01.533
Sir, it's not you.

00:15:02.467 --> 00:15:03.633
It's me!

00:15:04.267 --> 00:15:06.333
You need to hire
an assistant.

00:15:08.867 --> 00:15:11.267
Sir, I can walk away, right?

00:15:15.100 --> 00:15:16.167
[SIGHS]

00:15:16.367 --> 00:15:21.300
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:15:21.300 --> 00:15:22.633
[GLASS CLINKING]

00:15:22.633 --> 00:15:25.833
[Trixie] Ma,
you're not listening to me.

00:15:25.833 --> 00:15:27.433
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

00:15:27.433 --> 00:15:29.633
I'm listening.

00:15:29.633 --> 00:15:31.733
You said something about Miss...

00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:35.633
- Mister... Diaz?
- Yes. Mister...

00:15:35.667 --> 00:15:38.733
- Mister Diaz.
- And the boutique's design.

00:15:38.733 --> 00:15:40.600
Mom, you're not listening to me.

00:15:40.600 --> 00:15:43.567
- [GLASS CLATTERS]
- I'm sorry, Trixie.

00:15:43.567 --> 00:15:46.367
[TRIXIE] You're thinking
about Martin, aren't you?

00:15:46.367 --> 00:15:48.533
When he called, he
said he was fine.

00:15:50.133 --> 00:15:52.433
He said the same
thing to me.

00:15:52.433 --> 00:15:54.867
But I don't believe it.

00:15:54.867 --> 00:15:56.233
I mean...

00:15:56.233 --> 00:15:58.867
there's a lot of things
going on with your brother.

00:15:58.867 --> 00:16:01.367
And now, he's
living on that island.

00:16:01.367 --> 00:16:03.533
[GLASS CLATTERS]

00:16:03.533 --> 00:16:06.333
You're worried he'll have
a hard time because

00:16:06.333 --> 00:16:08.700
he didn't have a personal
assistant and

00:16:08.733 --> 00:16:10.500
he's not used to living there.

00:16:10.500 --> 00:16:14.300
- [EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SIGHS]

00:16:14.300 --> 00:16:17.700
Yeah. It looks like
we're both worried about hum.

00:16:20.367 --> 00:16:23.367
But I was thinking, Mom,
what if...

00:16:23.367 --> 00:16:26.167
what if I go to the island?

00:16:26.167 --> 00:16:27.633
But as a hotel guest...

00:16:29.533 --> 00:16:30.767
No.

00:16:33.333 --> 00:16:35.700
[LUNA] Justin, can we talk?

00:16:36.600 --> 00:16:39.633
[JUSTIN] Sure,
but can we talk after I chill?

00:16:39.633 --> 00:16:42.200
Justin, it's working hours!

00:16:42.233 --> 00:16:43.600
I am working!

00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:46.500
[SCOFFS] Do you really want
to call it work?

00:16:46.500 --> 00:16:49.300
I'm in charge of the
events and recreation.

00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:51.833
I'm just waiting for more work
for the music fest event.

00:16:51.833 --> 00:16:53.600
And this...

00:16:53.600 --> 00:16:55.200
is recreation!

00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:57.367
Come on, Justin.
I don't Martin to think

00:16:57.367 --> 00:16:58.933
that you're lazy.
That's enough.

00:16:58.933 --> 00:17:02.400
We have guests who wants
to swim and chill because of me.

00:17:02.400 --> 00:17:03.633
Right, girls?

00:17:04.600 --> 00:17:05.867
[CHUCKLES]

00:17:05.867 --> 00:17:07.433
Oh, yeah!

00:17:07.433 --> 00:17:09.333
Before I forget...

00:17:09.333 --> 00:17:11.300
I'm going
to take a day off, okay?

00:17:11.300 --> 00:17:13.933
You're not working,
yet you dare to take a leave?

00:17:13.933 --> 00:17:17.200
Jade's only here once a week
and that doesn't bother you.

00:17:17.233 --> 00:17:19.633
Jade's in dad's
outreach program.

00:17:19.633 --> 00:17:21.400
She's there right now.

00:17:21.400 --> 00:17:22.967
What are you going to do?

00:17:22.967 --> 00:17:24.767
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17:24.767 --> 00:17:26.667
Are you serious?

00:17:26.667 --> 00:17:27.867
What do you mean?

00:17:30.400 --> 00:17:31.967
Whatever.

00:17:31.967 --> 00:17:33.500
I'll just keep it to myself.

00:17:35.500 --> 00:17:37.467
[SIGHS]

00:17:40.567 --> 00:17:45.600
- [MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

00:17:47.333 --> 00:17:51.400
Your father will be furious if
he finds out I let you go there.

00:17:51.433 --> 00:17:55.033
You're not making me go there,
this is my decision.

00:17:55.033 --> 00:17:58.300
Trixie, can we not
argue about this.

00:17:58.300 --> 00:17:59.967
Because?

00:17:59.967 --> 00:18:02.667
You know your father
doesn't like that place.

00:18:02.667 --> 00:18:05.600
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

00:18:05.600 --> 00:18:07.900
I want to go to my brother.

00:18:07.900 --> 00:18:10.667
Ever since
his father died...

00:18:10.667 --> 00:18:13.600
I want to do something
nice for him and this is it.

00:18:15.033 --> 00:18:16.967
I going to Hotel 88.

00:18:24.800 --> 00:18:27.533
Sir, are you all right?

00:18:27.533 --> 00:18:29.567
Wait, is it your
birthday today, sir?

00:18:30.500 --> 00:18:32.400
No, it's tomorrow.

00:18:33.367 --> 00:18:34.467
But thank you.

00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:37.300
You're the only one
who remembers.

00:18:37.300 --> 00:18:38.767
All right, sir. Enjoy.

00:18:38.767 --> 00:18:41.700
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:41.700 --> 00:18:43.433
[GLASS CLATTERS]

00:18:54.800 --> 00:18:57.233
[MELLOW MUSIC
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

00:19:00.367 --> 00:19:02.367
[STAFF]
Sir, you need to go home.

00:19:02.633 --> 00:19:04.733
You said you can only
drink eight...

00:19:04.733 --> 00:19:07.200
No, no. Give me another one!

00:19:07.433 --> 00:19:09.067
I'm not drunk! Hurry up!

00:19:09.067 --> 00:19:11.267
Nah, man. He's drunk.

00:19:14.067 --> 00:19:15.500
[MAN 1] He's passed out!

00:19:16.467 --> 00:19:18.700
You heard about the idiots
who killed each other?

00:19:19.767 --> 00:19:22.367
The other one was Michael,
a playboy.

00:19:22.567 --> 00:19:27.000
He's so foul that he decided
to bed his friend's wife!

00:19:28.267 --> 00:19:31.300
[MAN 2] They should've shared.

00:19:32.700 --> 00:19:35.567
Hey, you.
What are you looking at?

00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:39.033
You think it's funny?
You're laughing, huh?

00:19:39.367 --> 00:19:41.633
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

00:19:42.433 --> 00:19:43.367
[BLOW LANDS]

00:19:44.067 --> 00:19:46.233
[STAFF] Sir! Sir, that's enough!

00:19:48.600 --> 00:19:51.033
[GRUNTS]

00:19:51.433 --> 00:19:52.567
- [GLASS BREAKS]
- [GROANS]

00:19:53.233 --> 00:19:54.167
Huh?!

00:19:54.500 --> 00:19:56.267
Come on, keep laughing!

00:19:56.467 --> 00:19:58.100
Your lives are a joke!

00:19:58.100 --> 00:20:00.300
All you do are gossip
about other people's lives!

00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:02.000
Huh?! Come on!

00:20:02.500 --> 00:20:03.533
Come on!

00:20:04.067 --> 00:20:05.400
Let me go!

00:20:05.400 --> 00:20:07.033
- [STAFF] That's enough!
- Huh?!

00:20:10.667 --> 00:20:12.367
Sir, the police are here.

00:20:14.367 --> 00:20:15.467
Sir Henry.

00:20:15.467 --> 00:20:17.700
We've been seeing each other
more often recently.

00:20:18.333 --> 00:20:20.500
I wish we didn't see
each other so often.

00:20:20.700 --> 00:20:23.733
Whenever we meet,
it means there's trouble.

00:20:26.467 --> 00:20:27.400
[SCOFFS]

00:20:32.067 --> 00:20:33.167
[FRIDA] What is this?

00:20:34.633 --> 00:20:35.667
Justin!

00:20:36.400 --> 00:20:37.800
Why do you have a black eye?

00:20:38.500 --> 00:20:39.667
The usual, Mom.

00:20:40.167 --> 00:20:41.433
He got into a fight at the bar.

00:20:42.233 --> 00:20:43.367
- Is that right, sir?
- Sit down.

00:20:43.367 --> 00:20:46.800
When they found out he's
an Almazan, they backed out.

00:20:46.800 --> 00:20:48.200
[FRIDA] Get me a cold compress!

00:20:48.567 --> 00:20:49.800
It's nothing new, sir.

00:20:50.333 --> 00:20:52.100
We'll talk to our lawyers
about it.

00:20:52.833 --> 00:20:55.600
Your brother
might still be mourning,

00:20:55.600 --> 00:20:57.067
that's why he got into a fight.

00:20:58.600 --> 00:21:00.567
I hope your family finds peace.

00:21:01.700 --> 00:21:02.733
Thank you.

00:21:05.333 --> 00:21:07.367
Justin,
what's going on with you?

00:21:07.367 --> 00:21:09.533
Why do you always
get into fights?

00:21:09.567 --> 00:21:12.700
Mom! It's nothing.
I'm gonna take a rest.

00:21:12.700 --> 00:21:13.867
- Justin!
- Justin!

00:21:14.467 --> 00:21:17.400
Justin, wait!
We're not done here!

00:21:18.700 --> 00:21:20.267
What's going on, Ma?

00:21:20.833 --> 00:21:23.700
The usual.
He got into a fight again.

00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:25.267
[SIGHS]

00:21:30.167 --> 00:21:31.133
Justin!

00:21:31.500 --> 00:21:32.467
What?!

00:21:34.200 --> 00:21:35.700
You're too old to be doing this.

00:21:36.333 --> 00:21:38.267
Picking fights at bars?

00:21:38.767 --> 00:21:39.733
[SCOFFS]

00:21:39.733 --> 00:21:41.667
You act like you're still
in high school.

00:21:45.833 --> 00:21:48.600
Why do you keep
worrying Mom so much?

00:21:49.700 --> 00:21:51.833
You know what
she's going through.

00:21:57.200 --> 00:21:58.467
This is the last time

00:21:58.667 --> 00:22:01.633
that our lawyer
will take care of your problem.

00:22:03.167 --> 00:22:04.133
Next time,

00:22:04.333 --> 00:22:07.333
find someone else
to bail you out.

00:22:11.400 --> 00:22:12.467
[DOOR SLAMS]

00:22:14.267 --> 00:22:16.933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

00:22:18.233 --> 00:22:20.100
[RAPHIE] Sir, would you like
some drinks?

00:22:21.233 --> 00:22:22.367
Breakfast, sir?

00:22:22.700 --> 00:22:24.233
You haven't eaten yet.

00:22:24.367 --> 00:22:25.533
My sister's cooking
is really good.

00:22:25.667 --> 00:22:27.100
[MARTIN] Raphie, I'm not hungry!

00:22:27.833 --> 00:22:28.767
Ah...

00:22:28.900 --> 00:22:30.200
Uh-- I got it!

00:22:30.333 --> 00:22:32.500
English breakfast?
Or Tagalog...

00:22:32.633 --> 00:22:34.300
- Or what--
- I don't want anything.

00:22:35.167 --> 00:22:38.333
What I need to know
is where my applicants are.

00:22:40.633 --> 00:22:43.233
- Raphie, did you post it?
- [SIGHS]

00:22:43.367 --> 00:22:45.533
Sir, I really posted it,
I promise.

00:22:45.667 --> 00:22:48.133
[MARTIN] Maybe--
Maybe what you said is wrong?

00:22:48.300 --> 00:22:50.500
I posted the correct
time and place

00:22:50.633 --> 00:22:52.200
so that many people would see

00:22:52.333 --> 00:22:53.733
that you're looking
for an assistant.

00:22:53.867 --> 00:22:57.033
So, why is it that until now,
none of them are here?

00:22:57.167 --> 00:22:58.200
Uh...

00:22:58.333 --> 00:23:00.400
Maybe they aren't
awake yet, sir?

00:23:00.533 --> 00:23:01.433
Sir, not everyone

00:23:01.567 --> 00:23:03.567
is an early bird
with the worm like you.

00:23:03.700 --> 00:23:05.867
[SIGHS HEAVILY]
It's impossible.

00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:07.333
It's possible, sir.

00:23:07.467 --> 00:23:09.767
It's really, really,
really, really possible.

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:13.400
[SIGHS] Where are they?

00:23:14.667 --> 00:23:16.467
[RAPHIE] He's really mad.

00:23:18.067 --> 00:23:19.500
[SARI] Universe!

00:23:19.633 --> 00:23:21.467
Please make it happen.

00:23:22.167 --> 00:23:23.733
Universe, give this to me.

00:23:23.867 --> 00:23:25.167
This is mine now, universe.

00:23:25.800 --> 00:23:27.400
Universe!

00:23:29.500 --> 00:23:31.867
Good morning, y'all!

00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:37.000
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

00:23:37.133 --> 00:23:38.400
[HENRI] This case
isn't done yet, Marina.

00:23:38.533 --> 00:23:42.000
I still need to know more about
Michael and Federico's deaths.

00:23:42.133 --> 00:23:44.033
Looks like Gio's going
to make some money.

00:23:44.167 --> 00:23:45.233
We can collect from that.

00:23:45.367 --> 00:23:46.567
Solara island?

00:23:47.133 --> 00:23:48.000
Here it is!

00:23:48.133 --> 00:23:51.333
Huh? They got someone else
at Hotel 88?

00:23:51.467 --> 00:23:52.867
You still have feelings
for me, huh?

00:23:55.733 --> 00:23:57.200
Is this what you mean?

00:23:58.433 --> 00:23:59.667
I need to see the beach.

00:23:59.800 --> 00:24:02.200
That should be included in
what I promote for Hotel 88.